---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Legal &mdash; Privacy Policy & Terms of Service" description="Privacy Policy and Terms of Service for OpenModeration by Logora.">
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-brand-50 to-white py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-surface-900 sm:text-5xl">Legal</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-surface-900">Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-surface-400">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm text-surface-600">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-surface-900">Logora</strong> (&quot;we&quot;, &quot;our&quot;, or &quot;us&quot;)
          operates the OpenModeration platform. This Privacy Policy explains how we handle
          your information when you use our self-hosted software or our managed cloud service.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Self-Hosted Deployment</h3>
        <p>
          When you deploy OpenModeration on your own infrastructure, we have zero access
          to your data. All content, moderation results, API keys, and configuration remain
          entirely on your servers. Your data never touches our systems.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Cloud Service (SaaS)</h3>
        <p>
          When you use our managed cloud service, we process:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Account information:</strong> email address, name, billing details.</li>
          <li><strong>Content submitted for moderation:</strong> text sent to the moderation API. Stored according to your configured data retention policy (default 7 days).</li>
          <li><strong>Moderation results:</strong> provider responses, scores, and decisions. Retained for audit trail purposes.</li>
          <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> request volume, latency, provider usage. Aggregated and anonymized for service improvement.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Data Retention</h3>
        <p>
          You control data retention. Configure `input_text_days` and `logs_days` in your
          OpenModeration.yaml. Default: 7 days for input text, 90 days for logs.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Data Security</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>All API traffic uses TLS 1.3 encryption in transit.</li>
          <li>Provider API keys are encrypted with AES-256-GCM at rest.</li>
          <li>Content text is encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM).</li>
          <li>API keys are hashed with SHA-256 in the database.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Third-Party Providers</h3>
        <p>
          When you use BYOK (Bring Your Own Keys), content is sent to your chosen provider
          (OpenAI, Azure, etc.) for moderation. Their privacy policies apply to that processing.
          When you use platform-managed keys, Logora sends content to providers on your behalf.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">Contact</h3>
        <p>
          For privacy inquiries: privacy@openmoderation.com
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="my-12 border-surface-200" />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-surface-900">Terms of Service</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-surface-400">Last updated: June 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm text-surface-600">
        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">1. Acceptance of Terms</h3>
        <p>By using OpenModeration (self-hosted or cloud), you agree to these terms.</p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">2. License (Self-Hosted)</h3>
        <p>
          The self-hosted version of OpenModeration is licensed under the
          <strong>GNU Affero General Public License v3 (AGPL v3)</strong>.
          You may use, modify, and distribute it in accordance with that license.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">3. Cloud Service</h3>
        <p>
          The managed cloud service is provided on a subscription basis. Usage is subject to
          rate limits based on your plan. We reserve the right to suspend service for
          accounts that violate our Acceptable Use Policy.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">4. Acceptable Use</h3>
        <p>You agree not to use OpenModeration for:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Any illegal activity or content</li>
          <li>Attempting to reverse-engineer provider APIs through the platform</li>
          <li>Circumventing rate limits or security measures</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">5. Disclaimer</h3>
        <p>
          OpenModeration is provided &quot;as is&quot; without warranty. We are not responsible
          for the accuracy of third-party provider moderation results. Moderation decisions
          are the responsibility of the platform operator.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-surface-900">6. Contact</h3>
        <p>For legal inquiries: legal@openmoderation.com</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>